Claims STATEMENT OF CLAIMS We claim: 1. A centrifugal clutch assembly (100) comprising: a rotatable member (104) connected to an input member (102); a plurality of first engaging members (106) movably engaged with said rotatable member (104); a driven member (112) freely mounted on an output member (120); a plurality of first retention members (110), each of said first retention member (110) engaged with corresponding said first engaging member (106), said first retention members (110) is adapted to be selectively at least one of engaged and disengaged with respect to said driven member (112); a plurality of second engaging members (114) movably engaged with said driven member (112); and a plurality of second retention members (118), each of said second retention member (118) is engaged with corresponding said second engaging member (114), said second retention members (118) is adapted to be selectively at least one of engaged and disengaged with respect to said output member (120). 2. The centrifugal clutch assembly (100) as claimed in claim 1, wherein said centrifugal clutch assembly (100) comprises, a plurality of first resilient members (108), where one end of each of said first resilient member (108) is connected to corresponding said first retention member (110) and another end of said first resilient member (108) is connected to corresponding said another first retention member (110); and a plurality of second resilient members (116), where one end of each of said second resilient member (116) is connected to corresponding said second engaging member (114) and another end of said second resilient member (116) is connected to corresponding said another second engaging member (114). 3. The centrifugal clutch assembly (100) as claimed in claim 2, wherein said plurality of first engaging members (106) moves said plurality of first retention members (110) towards said driven member (112) thereby engaging said plurality of first retention members (110) with said driven member (112) when the centrifugal force on said plurality of first engaging 

 members (106) exceeds the tensile force of said plurality of first resilient members (108) on rotational speed of said input member (102) reaching a first predetermined speed (SI); and said second engaging members (114) moves said second retention members (118) away from said output member (120) thereby disengaging said second retention members (118) from said output member (120) when centrifugal force on said second engaging members (114) exceeds the tensile force of said second resilient members (116) on rotational speed of said input member (102) reaching a second predetermined speed (S2). 4. The centrifugal clutch assembly (100) as claimed in claim 3, wherein said second engaging members (114) moves said plurality of second retention members (118) towards said output member (120) thereby engaging said second retention members (118) with said output member (120) when centrifugal forces on said second engaging members (114) reduces below the tensile forces of said second resilient means (116) on the rotational speed of said input member (102) is equal or less than the second predetermined speed (S2); and said first engaging members (104) moves said first retention members (110) away from said driven member (112) to dis-engage said first retention members (110) from said driven member (112) thereby disengaging said input member (102) from said output member (120) when the centrifugal forces on said first engaging members (106) reduces below the tensile forces of said first resilient means (108) on the rotational speed of said input member (102) is reduced below the first predetermined speed (SI). 5. The centrifugal clutch assembly (100) as claimed in claim 4, wherein said input member (102) is rotatably connected to a crankshaft (IOC) of an engine (10); said output shaft (120) is coupled to an air compressor of a supercharger (10S); said driven member (112) drives said output member (120) through said second engaging members (114) and said second retention members (118) on engagement of said first retention members (110) with said driven member (112); said input member (102), said rotatable member (104), said first engaging members (106) and said first retention members (110) forms driving section of said centrifugal clutch assembly (100); said driven member (112), said second engaging members (114), said second retention members (118) and said output member (120) forms driven section of said centrifugal clutch assembly (100); 

 the first predetermined speed (SI) of said input member (102) corresponds to a lower operating speed of the engine (10); and the second predetermined speed (S2) corresponds to a higher operating speed of the engine (10). 6. The centrifugal clutch assembly (100) as claimed in claim 5, wherein input member (102) is a pulley; said rotatable member (104) is a rotatable hub; each of said first engaging member (106) is a flyweight; each of said first retention member (110) is a liner; each of said resilient member (108) is a spring; said driven member (112) is a drum; each of said second engaging member (114) is a flyweight; each of said second resilient member (116) is a spring; each of said second retention member (118) is a liner; said output member (120) is an output shaft; and said driven section (said driven member (112), said second engaging members (114), said second retention members (118), said second resilient means (116) and said output member (120)) of said centrifugal clutch assembly (100) can be replaced by a âfreewheel clutch mechanism /one way clutch / overrunning clutch mechanismâ. 7. The centrifugal clutch assembly (100) as claimed in claim 5, wherein said driven member (112) is freely mounted onto said output member (120) through a bearing (103A); said input member (102) and said rotatable member (104) is freely mounted onto said driven member (112) through another bearing (103B); said rotatable member (104) is adapted to hold and support said first engaging members (106); each of said first engaging member (106) is positioned diametrically opposite to said other first engaging member (106) on said rotatable member (104); said first retention members (110) and said first resilient members (108) are adapted to retain said first engaging members (106) on said rotational member (104) at a predetermined position; each of said first retention member (110) is engaged with an outer portion of corresponding said first engaging member (106); 

 each of said second engaging member (114) is positioned diametrically opposite to said other second engaging member (114) in said driven member (112); said second resilient members (116) and said second retention members (118) are adapted to retain said second engaging members (114) in said driven member (112) at a predetermined position; and each of said second retention member (118) is engaged with an inner portion of corresponding said second engaging member (114). 8. The centrifugal clutch assembly (100) as claimed in claim 7, wherein said centrifugal clutch assembly (100) comprises a support member (105) secured to said output member (120), where support member (105) is adapted to support one end of said bearing (103 A), wherein said input member (102), said rotatable member (104), said first engaging members (106) and said first retention members (110) are freely rotating with respect to said output member (120); said driven member (112) is adapted to house said rotatable member (104), said first retention members (110), said first resilient members (108) and said first engaging members (106) at an input side; said driven member (112) is adapted to house said second retention members (118), the plurality of second resilient members (116) and said second engaging members (114) at an output side; each of said first engaging member (106) is located between said rotatable member (104) and corresponding said first retention member (110); said first retention member (110) are located between said first engaging members (106) and said driven member (112); each of said second engaging member (114) is located between said driven member (112) and corresponding said second retention member (118); and each of said second retention member (118) is located between said output member (120) and corresponding said second engaging member (114). 9. A method (200) of operation of a centrifugal clutch assembly (100), said method (200) comprising: driving, by an input member (102)